---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section
    id="hero"
    class="relative flex items-end justify-start h-screen bg-[#3D4A3A] h-[55vh]"
  >
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8 pb-8 text-left">
      <h2 class="text-white text-lg font-bold mb-2">
        <a href="/challenges" class="font-departure">Challenge</a> / 001
      </h2>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-8 text-white font-departure">
        Parks and Rec
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4">
        Use AI to build a visually compelling directory of the parks in your
        hometown
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Challenge Summary Section -->
  <section id="summary" class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Challenge Summary
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        The Parks and Rec Hackathon is a week-long creative sprint to build a
        new digital homepage for the parks in your hometown while leveraging AI
        to do it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        This isn't a technical competition. It's a creative one. You can build a
        map, a zine, a chatbot, a dreamy single-page site, or something that
        doesn't even look like a directory at all. The challenge on the table is
        to take a somewhat narrow scope and see how far you can push it
        creatively. There aren't many specific requirements, so use this to
        shine a light on the parks that make your city feel alive.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        Our goal with this challenge is to give you space to explore,
        experiment, and share your vision. Use the tools that excite you. Follow
        the threads that inspire you. Make something you're proud of — and
        surprise yourself along the way.
      </p>

      <!-- Seasonal Images Gallery -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <!-- Mobile Carousel (default) -->
        <div
          class="block md:hidden relative w-full overflow-x-auto snap-x snap-mandatory"
        >
          <div class="flex w-full gap-4 px-4">
            <div class="w-full flex-shrink-0 snap-center">
              <img
                src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/spring.png"
                alt="Spring"
                class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="w-full flex-shrink-0 snap-center">
              <img
                src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/summer.png"
                alt="Summer"
                class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="w-full flex-shrink-0 snap-center">
              <img
                src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/fall.png"
                alt="Fall"
                class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="w-full flex-shrink-0 snap-center">
              <img
                src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/winter.png"
                alt="Winter"
                class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Medium Screen Grid (2x2) -->
        <div class="hidden md:grid lg:hidden grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/spring.png"
            alt="Spring"
            class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/summer.png"
            alt="Summer"
            class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/fall.png"
            alt="Fall"
            class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/winter.png"
            alt="Winter"
            class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Large Screen Row with Tilted Images -->
        <div class="hidden lg:flex justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/spring.png"
            alt="Spring"
            class="w-1/4 h-auto max-h-[500px] object-contain transform -rotate-3"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/summer.png"
            alt="Summer"
            class="w-1/4 h-auto max-h-[500px] object-contain transform rotate-3"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/fall.png"
            alt="Fall"
            class="w-1/4 h-auto max-h-[500px] object-contain transform -rotate-3"
          />
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/winter.png"
            alt="Winter"
            class="w-1/4 h-auto max-h-[500px] object-contain transform rotate-3"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Inspiration Section -->
  <section id="inspiration" class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Inspiration
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        There's no right way to do this. Your "directory" could be functional,
        expressive, absurd, or all of the above. Below are some ideas to spark
        your thinking — but feel free to ignore them completely and make
        something that only you could make.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        You might build…
      </h3>

      <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8 mb-12">
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 mb-8 md:mb-0 text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]"
        >
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A minimalist web app that lists your city's parks with
              AI-generated photography</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A vintage 90s-style site with pixel art and fake park reviews</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span>A chatbot that speaks like a poetic park ranger</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A mobile app with park trail maps, a "catch 'em all" feature for
              local plants and wildlife, and an AI park ranger to guide you on a
              narrated walk</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A dreamy photo zine with DALL·E images and short, AI-generated
              haikus</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span>A 3D map with custom icons and ambient soundscapes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A searchable directory of local parks by mood ("quiet," "sunny,"
              "best for dog naps")</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
            <span
              >A print-on-demand coffee table book of the most beautiful parks
              you've never heard of</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div
          class="flex justify-center md:justify-start lg:justify-center md:items-start"
        >
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/birds.png"
            alt="Decorative bird illustration"
            class="w-full max-w-md h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        If you're using AI for visuals, try Midjourney, DALL·E, Runway, or
        custom-trained models. For websites and apps, tools like Vercel,
        Supabase, and GPT-4 can get you far. But we're tool-agnostic — whatever
        helps bring your idea to life is fair game.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Guidelines Section -->
  <section id="guidelines" class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Guidelines
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        This hackathon is intentionally loose — but a little structure helps.
        Here's what you need to know:
      </p>

      <ul
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8 text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]"
      >
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Solo or teams:</span> You can work alone or
            with up to 3 others.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Use AI:</span> Your project should incorporate
            AI in some meaningful way — for visuals, code, text, interaction, or
            something else.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Make it local:</span> Focus on parks from your
            hometown, current city, or anywhere you feel a personal connection to.
            Interpret "park" as loosely as you like.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Publish it:</span> Host your project somewhere
            shareable — a website, a repo, a PDF zine, whatever works.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Tell us about it:</span> Submissions include
            a link and a short write-up: what you made, what tools you used, and
            why you're proud of it.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Be good to each other:</span> This is a creative
            space. Be generous with your ideas, kind with your feedback, and supportive
            of the weird and wonderful.</span
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Schedule Section -->
  <section id="schedule" class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Schedule
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        The hackathon runs for one week, with optional live sessions along the
        way. Here's how it breaks down:
      </p>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-[1600px] mx-auto"
      >
        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#4A6FA5] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Kickoff Call
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            We'll start with a short kickoff call to walk through the challenge,
            share ideas, and get inspired.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium">Monday, April 14 at 1:00 PM CT</span><br
              />
              <span class="text-sm">(2:00 PM ET / 11:00 AM PT)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#3D4A3A] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Hackathon Begins
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Start building. Share early ideas, sketches, and prototypes in
            Discord.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium"
                >Right after the kickoff call on April 14</span
              >
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#E2B93B] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Studio Hours
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Optional live session for feedback and jamming on ideas.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium">Tuesday, April 15 at 11:00 AM CT</span
              ><br />
              <span class="text-sm">(12:00 PM ET / 9:00 AM PT)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#E2B93B] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Studio Hours
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Optional live session for feedback and jamming on ideas.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium">Wednesday, April 16 at 2:00 PM CT</span
              ><br />
              <span class="text-sm">(3:00 PM ET / 12:00 PM PT)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#C94C4C] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Submissions Due
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Share a link to your project and a short write-up. A submission form
            will be shared near the end of the hackathon.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium">Sunday, April 20 at 2:00 PM CT</span><br
              />
              <span class="text-sm">(3:00 PM ET / 12:00 PM PT)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-[#4A6FA5] shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            Showcase & Wrap-Up
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            We'll give everyone a chance to show off what they built and
            announce the final awards.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center text-[#5F6368] dark:text-[#9AA0A6]">
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-lg">
              <span class="font-medium">Monday, April 21 at 11:00 AM CT</span
              ><br />
              <span class="text-sm">(12:00 PM ET / 9:00 AM PT)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Studio Hours Section -->
  <section id="studio" class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Studio Hours
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        Think of it like putting your project up on the wall: you'll get
        reactions, suggestions, and maybe even a new idea or direction you
        hadn't considered. You're welcome to come with something polished or
        totally in-progress.
      </p>

      <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
            This week's Studio Hours:
          </h3>

          <ul
            class="space-y-3 mb-8 lg:mb-0 text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]"
          >
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
              <span>
                <span class="font-bold">Tuesday, April 15 at 11:00 AM CT</span
                ><br />
                <span class="text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] opacity-80"
                  >(12:00 PM ET / 9:00 AM PT)</span
                >
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
              <span>
                <span class="font-bold">Wednesday, April 16 at 2:00 PM CT</span
                ><br />
                <span class="text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] opacity-80"
                  >(3:00 PM ET / 12:00 PM PT)</span
                >
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          class="flex justify-center lg:justify-start xl:justify-center lg:items-start"
        >
          <img
            src="/src/assets/img/challenges/001/studio-hours.png"
            alt="Studio Hours illustration"
            class="w-full max-w-md h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        Links will be shared in Discord before each session. You don't need to
        prepare anything formal — just bring what you've got and be ready to see
        what others are building too.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Prizes and Recognition Section -->
  <section id="prizes" class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5] font-departure"
      >
        Prizes and Recognition
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        While this isn't a traditional competition, we still want to celebrate
        great work.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        At the end of the week, we'll highlight a few standout projects during
        the Showcase. Recognition is based on creativity, execution, and that
        unnameable spark that makes something memorable. Think of these as
        community shoutouts.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        We'll be recognizing projects these categories:
      </h3>

      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 text-lg text-[#1C1C1C] dark:text-[#E5E5E5]">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-[#D4A73A] dark:text-[#D4A73A] mr-2">›</span>
          <span
            ><span class="font-bold">Best Overall</span> – the project that nails
            concept, execution, and style</span
          >
